dublin_core.dcvalue: In France the challenges of replacing departing psychiatrists with a new generation are compounded by an increased demand for psychiatric care which threatens the accessibility of health care particularly in rural and semi rural areas The objective of this study was to describe the location of psychiatrists trained in the Franche Comt region and to analyze the factors associated with establishing their practice in the region particularly in the most understaffed areas
[Demography of psychiatrists and attractiveness factors: the example of Franche-Comté].
